<h1>The Report of the National Commission on Marihuana and Drug
Abuse </h1>

<h2>Marihuana: A Signal of Misunderstanding </h2>

<p><b>Commissioned by President Richard M. Nixon, March, 1972</b>
</p>

<hr>

<p><b><u>Table of Contents</u></b> </p>

<h3>The Report </h3>

<p>Letter of Transmittal </p>

<p><a href="misintro.htm">Introduction</a> </p>

<p><a href="mis2.htm"><b>I. Marihuana and the Problem of
Marihuana</b></a><b><u> </u></b></p>

<ul>
    <li>Origins of the Marihuana Problem <ul>
            <li>Visibility </li>
            <li>Perceived Threats </li>
            <li>Symbolism </li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>The Need for Perspective <ul>
            <li>Historical Perspective </li>
            <li>Cultural Perspective <ul>
                    <li>The Search for Meaning </li>
                    <li>Skepticism </li>
                    <li>The Limits of Rationality </li>
                </ul>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>Formulating Marihuana Policy <ul>
