<p>BUREAU OF NARCOTICS, U.S. TREASURY DEP'T, TRAFFIC IN OPIUM AND
OTHER DANGEROUS DRUGS 63 (1935) [hereinafter cited as TRAFFIC IN
Opium]; id. at 90 (1936); id. at 81 (1937); Part of the erratic
quality of these figures may stem from failure to weigh only the
dried flowering tops of the plants seized. For example, 256
pounds seized in 1937 may represent a larger quantity of total
plants than 391,787 pounds seized in 1935. See Mandel, supra note
2, at 999.<br>
</p>

