<p>The Commission additionally has contracted a study of 105
selected, middle class, young, working adults from California,
who are marihuana smokers. Of this sample, 11% were daily
marihuana users and 47% used it several times a week; 33% used it
several times a month; 6% used it once to several times a year;
and 3% had used it but were not currently using marihuana. The
study indicates that while most of the subjects were frequent
marihuana users, the incidence of other drug use was relatively
low (Table 4).<br>
</p>

